content.div:
The third time may be the charm, but it looks like Britney Spears is going to have to wait a little while longer before Jason Trawick puts a (wedding) ring on it.

According to RadarOnline, Spears is delaying her nuptials because her lawyers first want to deal with the trial involving Sam Lufti (who was Brit's manager during her meltdown and who is currently suing her for breach of contract and her parents for libel and defamation.)

So far, Spears' legal hounds have managed to keep the pop star from bring deposed or called as a witness in the hearing, which is set for Sept. 11, but sources say that if she were to marry Trawick, things could change drastically.

A source explained to RadarOnline, "Lawyers for Britney's conservatorship have been successful in keeping her from being deposed in the Lutfi litigation...She could get married under the conservatorship, but the judge would have to sign off on it. If that were to happen, lawyers repping Lutfi would absolutely go into court and argue that if Britney were able to get married, she should be able to be deposed. There is no way Team Spears is going to let that happen.”

“The wedding will most likely be a very low key affair, and could take place in Britney's hometown in Louisiana, at her mansion in Kentwood,” the source added. “Jason is fully embracing having the wedding in Louisiana. Britney has hired a wedding planner and is letting the pro handle all the details. Unless a settlement is reached with Lutfi before the trial date, the wedding will take place after the lawsuit is resolved. Britney and Jason aren't in a rush to get married, they are enjoying being engaged....Britney already feels like she is married to him, and trusts him.”
